<h1 id="cc-page-title">Childcare as Infrastructure</h1>
<p class="report-hero-deck">A cross-country look at public childcare, the US gap, and what it would take to close it.</p>
<p class="report-hero-byline">Brian Dew</p>
</div>
<p class="report-hero-meta">~18 min read</p>
</div>
<main id="main">
<section>
<article class="prose prose-report cc-page">

<p class="report-abstract">A public childcare system is infrastructure. It removes a cost from families and boosts parental employment. Public childcare also unlocks the professional childcare workforce needed to meet demand and maintain high quality. This report compares childcare systems between the US and Nordic countries, at the national and state level.</p>

